awards:
[{'title': 'Top 4% best students in an international project.', 'description': 'X-Culture is a large-scale international experiential learning project that involves over 4,000
MBA and business students from over 100 universities from 40 countries on six continents
every semester. The students are placed in global virtual teams of about seven, each student
coming from a different country. Working with people from around the globe and dealing
with cultural differences, time-zone dispersion, and global communication challenges, the
teams complete a consulting project for a multi-national company.!

Compared to the other 4,000+ participants this semester, Zohair Zouitni’s
individual performance was better than that of 96.0 % of the other project participants, or it
was in Top 4.0%.!', 'issuer': 'X-culture', 'date': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, {'title': 'Business plan finalist (MoodSwing)', 'description': 'The name of our company is called Elysian Fields and is made up of 7 international business students who are currently studying at the HAN (Arnhem Business School) in the Netherlands. The concept behind the name Elysian Fields is based on ancient Greek mythology, which refers to the final resting place of the heroic and the virtuous. According to Homer, an ancient Greek poet, the Elysian Fields or Elysium was place where the favored of Zeus enjoyed perfect happiness.

Today’s world can be demanding and stressful and so understanding this, we have developed a product that can help make ones experience in this world a lot more pleasant. Enter the Mood Swing. With the Mood Swing one does not have to wait until they reach the afterlife to enjoy perfect happiness and a stress free environment. This product is designed to release natural aromatic fragrances in the air and help boost moods and provide a feeling of calmness in the midst of busy days.

The Elysian Fields’ Mood Swing is an essential oil diffuser that works in conjunction with mood sensor, which is in the form of a wristband. With this product, we have combined aromatherapy with technology. We have created a symbiotic relationship between nature and technology. The mood sensor is the key element of our product. It is what separates us from the rest of the pack. How the sensor works is, it senses a person’s mood by reading their temperature and monitoring their nerve impulses. After a reading is done and a mood is detected, that mood is then wirelessly communicated to the electric oil diffuser, telling it to release a fragrance that compliments the state of mind a person might be in. Have a look, I hope our little magazine will also be useful for you to read and learn from other experts to further enhance your business practices.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Zohair', 'last_name': 'Zouitni', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Onderwijs | Sociale mobiliteit | Financiën '}, {'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Rafi', 'last_name': 'Kasermali', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Client Advisor at Tiffany & Co.'}]}, {'title': 'Market Research Project - Euro-Com', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'description': "During this project, as part of our study, we were asked to carry-out a market research project for the Dutch translation company Euro-Com. In order for Euro-Com to maintain their ISO-certificate, research with regard to the customer satisfaction is required.

In order to perform efficient data gathering, a research tool had to be created. As preferred by Euro-Com, a telephone survey was used to contact the vast majority of Euro-Com's customers.
The questions within this survey covered the following subjects upon customer satisfaction: service, product, communication and problem solving abilities of the company. Next to the telephone surveys, face-to-face interviews were conducted with five of Euro-Com's customers.
